# Other agent harnesses' local config — operator WIP, not this repo's scaffold.
# Untracked files are invisible to the driver's dirty-tree guard
# (`_expected_flip_paths` / `_tracked_dirty_paths` inspect TRACKED paths only),
# but the per-WU squash commit stages everything — so anything untracked in the
# tree gets absorbed by whichever WU commits first. FEAT-2026-0031/T01 swept both
# of these onto its feature branch that way. Ignoring is a stopgap; the real fix
# is narrowing the squash commit's staging to match the guard's inspection.
AGENTS.md
.codex/

# FEAT-2026-0020 gh-content audit dumps — contain private-org refs, must NOT be committed (would leak into public history)
.specfuse/features/FEAT-2026-0020-public-readiness-prep/gh-issues.json
.specfuse/features/FEAT-2026-0020-public-readiness-prep/gh-prs.json
.specfuse/features/FEAT-2026-0020-public-readiness-prep/gh-redacted/
.specfuse/features/FEAT-2026-0020-public-readiness-prep/history-scrub/
